al citadels group of hedge funds rank among the largest and most successful hedge funds in the world forbes identified griffin as one of s highest earning hedge fund managers as well as one of the forbes  as of may update griffin had an estimated net worth of us billion at the beginning of  griffin made a  million donation to the financial aid program at harvard university his alma mater the largest single donation ever made to the institution at the time and his donations to various organizations and causes have totaled about  million contents  early life and education  investment career  citadel  political and economic views  views on market structure  personal life  wealth and philanthropy  art collection  legacy and awards  see also  references  further reading  external links early life and educationedit kenneth c griffin was born in  in daytona beach florida in high school he excelled academically while also being the president of his math club in  griffin started to invest during his freshman year at harvard university after reading a forbes magazine article during his second year at harvard he started a hedge fund focused on convertible bond arbitrage the fund was capitalized with  from friends and family including money from his grandmother he installed a satellite link to his dorm to acquire realtime market data the investment strategy helped preserve capital during the stock market crash of  griffins early success enabled him to launch a second fund and between the two funds he was managing just over  million griffin graduated from harvard in  with a degree in economics investment careeredit after graduating from harvard frank c meyer an investor and founder of glenwood capital llc provided griffin with  million to invest griffin exceeded meyers expectations and according to the new york times meyer made  percent return on the investment citadeledit in  griffin founded citadel with  million by  citadel had grown to a team of more than  employees and  billion in investment capital in june  griffin was included in cfo magazines global  a list of the most influential people in the world of finance griffin has appeared numerous times in forbes forbes  first in  with an estimated net worth of  million at  he was the youngest selfmade individual on the list in september  fortune magazine ranked griffin who was  that year as the eighth richest american under forty in the category of selfmade united statesbased wealth in  griffin was the fifth youngest of the seven members under the age of  listed on the forbes  in  griffin had an estimated net worth of  billion by  griffin’s net worth was estimated at  billion in march  citadel received a top  great workplaces in financial services ranking by the great places to work institute based on a survey by citadel employees griffin was credited for implementing a collaborative work culture and providing perks to employees including free lunch museum tours fitness programs and personal gifts griffin was a featured panelist at the  milken institute global conference where he spoke about citadel building complex organizations by investing in employees and corporate activism in which he said i’m all in favor of liberating access to the boardroom by activists and giving shareholders a greater role in how the company is managed that benefit accrues to everyone in societyimportance political and economic viewsedit griffin serves on the committee on capital markets regulation griffin is also a member of the g a network of  ceos that meets periodically to discuss the global economy in  griffin said in an interview with the chicago tribune that he was a reagan republican he said this belief that a larger government is what creates prosperity that a larger government is what creates good is wrong after the – financial crisis griffin made political contributions and donations to political candidates parties and organizations that supported his views of limited government such as american crossroads the republican governors association and restore our future a super pac that supported mitt romneys presidential bid griffin backed mitt romneys  run for the presidency and has donated to former us representative eric cantor republican of virginia and senator mark kirk republican of illinois he donated  million to bruce rauner a republican candidate for illinois governor in december  griffin endorsed sen marco rubio for the  republican presidential nomination and stated that he planned to donate millions to a prorubio super pac before this endorsement griffin had donated  each to three super pacs supporting rubio jeb bush and scott walker for the gop nomination in  griffin donated  million to conservative solutions pac freedom partners action fund right to rise usa and future views on market structureedit in  griffin voiced his stance on issues on financial regulations and market structure and has testified at various government hearings in  he gave testimony at a us senate committee  hearing on the role of regulation in shaping equity market structure and electronic trading in which he reiterated the need to have industry regulations catch up with the changes in market structure to increase the fairness and resilience of american equity markets griffin along with nasdaq executive vice president thomas a whittman and jeff sprecher founder and ceo of intercontinental exchange and the nyse has voiced concerns about regulation failing to keep pace with changes in market structure as in the practice of dark pools discriminating against certain customer segments in may  griffin criticized the risk management practices of wall street saying as an industry we have a responsibility to manage risk in a way that is prudent  the capital markets are controlled by a bunch of rightoutof business school young guys who havent really seen that much you have a real lack of wisdom griffin has also stated we as an industry dropped the ball the industry needs to overhaul its thinking accept greater regulation he explained his views on regulation and risk in a  new york times article where he was quoted as saying the unwillingness of the federal reserve and the sec to require working capital limits only exacerbates the risktaking environment because the banks are playing the equivalent of nolimit poker later in  he testified to the united states house committee on oversight and government reform stating that the rapid growth in the use of derivatives has created an opaque market whose outstanding notional value is measured in the hundreds of trillions of dollars as a result there is great concern about the systemic effects of the failure of any one financial institution personal lifeedit griffin married his first wife katherine weingartt who he had met in high school griffin later married anne diasgriffin the founder of aragon global management another chicagobased hedge fund firm in july  with whom he had three children griffin and his wife later divorced in october  citing irreconcilable differences he is a member of the fourth presbyterian church of chicago in  griffin donated  million of the  million needed to build a new chapel at the church the modern building is called the gratz center in honor of griffins grandparents in  he acquired four real estate properties in palm beach florida that cost a cumulated sum of  million in  griffin was elected to a fiveyear term on the university of chicagos board of trustees he is a member of the board of trustees for the art institute of chicago the museum of contemporary art and the whitney museum of american art he is also a member of a number of organizations including the economic club of chicago and the civic committee of the commercial club of chicago griffin serves as the vice chairman of the chicago public education fund wealth and philanthropyedit in  griffin made contributions to the robin hood foundation in october  the griffins and the bill and melinda gates foundation funded and supported the opening of a new charter school in chicago called woodlawn high school in  griffin donated a  million addition to the art institute of chicago that was designed by renzo piano the paul cézanne paintings have also been loaned to the institute in october  griffin and his wife founded the kenneth and anne griffin foundation the foundations contributions include  million for the chicago heights early childhood center  million to childrens memorial hospital funding the university of chicago’s early childhood center and others the chicago heights early childhood center located in chicago heights illinois is an experimental educational effort run by economics professor john a list from university of chicago to test whether investing in teachers or in parents produces better student performance in school as of update griffin had contributed to the art institute of chicago public education the childrens memorial hospital in chicago the chicago public library and the chicago symphony orchestra griffin also contributed to the museum of contemporary art the evolving planet at the field museum of natural history and endowed professorships at the university of chicago in february  griffin gave  million to harvard university his alma mater largely for needbased undergraduate financial aid at the time it was the largest single gift in harvards history as of november update griffin had donated about  million to support various causes including tens of millions to institutions in chicago art collectionedit griffin is one of the most active art buyers in the world in  he paid a record price of  million for paul cézannes painting curtain jug and fruit bowl in october  griffin purchased false start by artist jasper johns for  million from dreamworks cofounder david geffen as of february update griffin had purchased willem de koonings  oil painting interchange for  million and jackson pollock’s  painting number a for  million both from david geffen in  griffin donated  million to the museum of contemporary art in chicago in december  he donated an unrestricted gift of  million to the museum of modern art in new york one of the single largest in the history of the museum legacy and awardsedit in  he was inducted into institutional investors alphas hedge fund manager hall of fame along with david swensen louis bacon steven cohen seth klarman paul tudor jones george soros michael steinhardt jack nash james simmons alfred jones leon levy julian roberston and bruce kovner see alsoedit list of harvard university alumni referencesedit  a b c delevingne lawrence may   king ken recovered citadel chief takes the hedge fund throne cnbc retrieved may     a b c d allen susie huang wen july   two new members elected to university of chicago board of trustees university of chicago news retrieved january     about citadels leadership citadel archived from the original on january   retrieved january     a b kapos shia march   not the ken griffin story you were expecting crains chicago business retrieved april     bit kelly october   griffins citadel rose in september as hedge funds fell bloomberg retrieved december     ken griffins citadel sees huge surge in assets cnbc october   retrieved february     nathan vardi february   the  highestearning hedge fund managers and traders forbes retrieved january     svea herbstbayliss february   hedge fund manager griffin gives  million to harvard reuters retrieved january     melissa harris february   billionaire chicagoan ken griffin donates  million to harvard chicago tribune retrieved january     a b c d e f meyer graham june   the file on citadels ken griffin chicago magazine retrieved november     a b ken griffin esquire october   retrieved january     paul milnes april   ken griffin – wall streets boy wonder hedgethink retrieved january     sheelah kolhatkar april   opening up the citadel upstart business journal retrieved january     kenneth griffin the worlds richest people forbescom february   retrieved augus